In the anelastic benchmark paper,  Jones et al 2011, Icarus 216 p 120-135
the equations are the same as used in the unified version, so no rescaling is required.
 Ra_unified = 8.0d04. Pr=1, Pm=50, E=0.002, radius ratio =0.35. The basic state is 
a polytrope with all the mass concentrated at the centre, the reference state model being in planet_model.txt.in,
generated by matlab script anelastic_benchmark. 
 
At i_N=128 i_L=128 and i_Mp=1, i_M=128  the solution has 7-fold symmetry, multiples
of m=7 (see the mag_spectrum_0002.dat file) and is steady in the drifting frame.

As given in the paper, KE_unified 4.194d05 and ME_unified=3.2018d05. The agreement is 
satisfactory for this resolution. 
Note that the timestep needs to be less than 1d-06 to get accurate agreement,
which means that d_corr_upper and d_corr_lower need to be in the region of 0.02
and 0.002 respectively.   


